1. What is Repeating? (The Core Pipeline)
Almost 80% of the work is identical in both questions. Both exercises require the exact same foundational PySpark ML workflow:

Initializing Spark & Loading Data: Reading the CSV from HDFS into a Spark DataFrame.

Preprocessing (Feature Engineering): Handling nulls, converting categorical text data into numbers, and merging all features into a single vector.

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA): Using basic DataFrame operations (groupBy, describe, show) to find trends.

Classification Training: Splitting the data and training a model (like Random Forest or Logistic Regression) to predict a categorical outcome (Churn = Yes/No, Promotion = Yes/No).

Evaluation: Testing the model's accuracy.

The ONLY difference: * Exercise 1 adds a Regression task (predicting a continuous number: Salary).

Exercise 2 adds a Deployment step (saving the model for future use).

