Exercise 3: CSV Sales Data with DataFrames
You will need to import col from pyspark.sql.functions to do math on columns.

Python
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql.functions import col

spark = SparkSession.builder.appName("SalesProcess").getOrCreate()

# 1. Read CSV
df = spark.read.csv("hdfs:///user/data/sales.csv", header=True, inferSchema=True)

# 2. Compute total revenue (Create a new column using withColumn)
df_revenue = df.withColumn("Revenue", col("Price") * col("Quantity"))

# 3. Find highest-selling product by revenue
highest_selling = df_revenue.orderBy(col("Revenue").desc()).limit(1)
highest_selling.show()

# 4. Filter transactions > $500
high_value_sales = df_revenue.filter(col("Revenue") > 500)

# 5. Group by category and sum revenue
category_revenue = df_revenue.groupBy("Category").sum("Revenue")

# 6. Save back as CSV
category_revenue.write.mode("overwrite").csv("hdfs:///user/data/sales_output", header=True)
